//-->
</script>
<script type="text/javascript"
src="http://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/show_ads.js">
</script>
</div>
		        <p>
		          <p align="left">I boiled sugar and corn syrup in one pot and in the other pot combined the remaining ingredients.  I used lemon juice and three packets of Kool-Aid to make it as sour as possible, since that is of course the most important part of a Sour Patch Kid.</p>
<p align="center"><img src="http://www.pimpthatsnack.com/images/projects/sourpatchkid/06.jpg" width="500"></p>

<p align="left">In the mold, setting for 24 hours:</p>
<p align="center"><img src="http://www.pimpthatsnack.com/images/projects/sourpatchkid/07.jpg" width="500"></p>

<p align="left">After coming out of the mold-- lookin delicious, little man!</p>
<p align="center"><img src="http://www.pimpthatsnack.com/images/projects/sourpatchkid/08.jpg" width="500"></p>

<p align="left">I did some research into the sour sugar they put on Sour Patch Kids -- it's made of sugar and citric acid.  I don't have much citric acid lying around, so I used some lemon Koolaid with the sugar to make it sour.  Turns out citric acid is the main ingredient of Kool-Aid.  Who knew acid could be so delicious??</p>
<p align="center"><img src="http://www.pimpthatsnack.com/images/projects/sourpatchkid/09.jpg" width="500"></p>

<p align="left">It was hard to get the sugar evenly distributed since the moisture from my baby kept soaking the sugar up, but it looked pretty good in the end…<p>
<p align="center"><img src="http://www.pimpthatsnack.com/images/projects/sourpatchkid/10.jpg" width="500"></p>

<p align="left">And now I must decide what the hell I'm supposed to do with a foot long Sour Patch Kid…</p>
<p align="center"><img src="http://www.pimpthatsnack.com/images/projects/sourpatchkid/11.jpg" width="500"></p>      </p>
